<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
2.6-3.6 mm long (mean = 2.84 mm; n = 5); 2.15-2.5
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the larger size, declivity extremely flat and broad; especially laterally; posterolateral declivital margin elevated, carinate; declivital surface covered with minute star-shaped scales.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
